description:
&lt;p&gt;Antimicrobial stewardship supported by the LTH tap on the bugs app, electronic prescribing with dedicated antimicrobial order sets, a well established antimicrobial management group, a warm friendly MDT that recognises the pivotal role pharmacy has to offer. Strong relationships with the infection control team and primary care antimicrobial lead. A dedicated OPAT team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If all of this excites you then you could be the next antimicrobial pharmacist to take on the challenges that lie ahead. In a year where infection prevention has never been far from our minds there are opportunities that can really allow your pharmacy skills to shine: Conserving antibiotics, guiding the use of emerging antivirals, supporting covid clinical trials, working innovatively to develop the MDT approach.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A prescribing qualification is desirable, however a successful candidate will be supported through the NMP course where necessary. The role is supported by an experienced dedicated antimicrobial management technician and with access to a team of directorate pharmacist prescribing leads, EPMA pharmacist and pharmacy procurement, clinical trials and medicines governance team, you are never far from a helping hand. Formal opportunities to develop a rising star can be aligned to a candidates needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If interested please see contacts for an informal discussion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date: Tuesday 24th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
